Rozo cloud filesystem : A clustered NAS using erasure coding.

* WARNING *
Rozo is currently on heavy developpement and release at alpha stage 
Don't use rozo under production environment 
* WARNING *

Note : [xxx] are optional, <xxx> are parameters

INSTALLATION
============ 

Requirements
------------
    - Cmake
    - libattr
    - libuuid
    - libconfig
    - libfuse
    - libpthread

Quick start
-----------
Using default values will compile rozo in Release mode and install it on /usr/local

mkdir build
cd build
cmake -G [-DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/foo/bar -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug] "Unix Makefiles" ../
make
[sudo] make install

Options (CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX, CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE...) of generated build tree can be modified with : make edit_cache

uninstall
---------

make uninstall

RUNNING
=======

Requirements
------------
    - a running portmap see portmap(8)
    - extend attributes on used file system (exports and storages) see mount(8) and fstab(5)

Start
-----

    1 ) install exportd on a host
    2 ) install storaged on multiple hosts
    3 ) create exported directory with exportd --create
    4 ) fill in export.conf (/etc/rozo or /usr/local/etc/rozo accordind to CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX)
    5 ) fill in all storage.conf
    6 ) [sudo] exportd --start
    7 ) [sudo] storaged --start
    8 ) wherever you want : [sudo] rozomount <the_host_running_exportd> <the export_name> <the_mount_dir>

Stop
----
    1) [sudo] exportd --stop
    2) [sudo] storaged --stop
    3) [sudo] umount <the_mount_dir>

